trans-unit.source: Allow guests with a valid reservation only
trans-unit.target: Allow guests with a valid reservation only

If activated, only guests with a valid reservation number have access to the services of the HotelGuest/APP. Other guests with an installed iOS or Android App on their devices are not able to use the services.

trans-unit.source: Seperate target groups between member and guests with a valid reservation
trans-unit.target: Separate target groups between member and guests with a valid reservation
If activated, all guest notifications and services in the HotelAppManager are provided with a selection box to target messages and services to different target groups.

The HotelGuestApp can be operated bilingually if required. In this case, the guest will see contents depending on their profile or browser settings. Activating this function ensures that all content related fields within the HotelAppManager are bilingual entered and forwarded.
Endpoint URL for hotels and regions

A valid API endpoint for loading hotels and regions must be specified and the intervals at which the data is updated by the external system must be defined. Without a correct API endpoint, the HotelGuest/APP will not work properly.
